From: amphetamine <amphetamine@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] ntdll: Export __wine_unix_call as PE-callable stdcall function

Port wine-valve's compat___wine_unix_call export. This exposes
__wine_unix_call as a proper PE DLL export that third-party PE code
(such as EasyAntiCheat's start_protected_game.exe) can resolve via
GetProcAddress or import table. The function dispatches through
__wine_unix_call_dispatcher to unix_call_funcs on the Unix side.

Without this export, PE code cannot invoke Wine's Unix layer through
the unix_call mechanism. EAC uses this to call load_so_dll
(unix_call_funcs[0]) for loading the native anti-cheat module.

--- a/dlls/ntdll/loader.c
+++ b/dlls/ntdll/loader.c
@@ -3486,6 +3486,15 @@
 }


+/***********************************************************************
+ *              __wine_unix_call
+ */
+NTSTATUS WINAPI compat___wine_unix_call( unixlib_handle_t handle, unsigned int code, void *args )
+{
+    return __wine_unix_call( handle, code, args );
+}
+
+
 /***********************************************************************
  *           __wine_unix_spawnvp
  */
--- a/dlls/ntdll/ntdll.spec
+++ b/dlls/ntdll/ntdll.spec
@@ -1749,6 +1749,7 @@
 # Unix interface
 @ stdcall __wine_unix_spawnvp(long ptr)
 @ stdcall __wine_ctrl_routine(ptr)
+@ stdcall __wine_unix_call(int64 long ptr) compat___wine_unix_call
 @ extern -private __wine_syscall_dispatcher
 @ extern -private __wine_unix_call_dispatcher
 @ extern -private -arch=arm64ec __wine_unix_call_dispatcher_arm64ec
